Without a doubt, tentacles: enter the dolphin is a fun and quirky game. The games controls are very well made and the art design overall is nice and not too "out there" there are a few gripes I have with the game though, for one: the stages all feel the same, every stage has spikes, spinning spikes and other generic threats. In a platformer or in this case a puzzle platformer hybrid, I expect difference between, say, stage 1 & 5. But no, every stage feels like the last. I would also say trying to get all 3 stars is pointless and should not be a burden to commit. Overall, tentacles: enter the dolphin is a nice little 0.99 cent game to add to your collection if you want to play something out of the norm.
